claims:
1. An electrically switchable antiferromagnetic device, the device comprising:
(a) a device body with at least one neck extending radially from the body, said body formed from crystalline FexNbS2;
(b) one or more write in electrodes mounted to said device body, said electrodes configured to be electrically coupled to a source of current; and
(c) one or more read out electrodes mounted to said neck of said device body, said read out electrode configured to measure a resistance state of said device body at said neck;
(d) wherein an antiferromagnetic order of said device body rotates with the application of current to said write in electrode from said current source.

3. The device of claim 1, further comprising:
a second read out electrode, said electrode configured to measure resistance at a center of the device body;
wherein a non-local resistance signal is measured by the read out electrode at the neck and a local resistance signal is measured with the second read out electrode.

5. The device of claim 4, further comprising:
a third read out electrode, said third electrode configured to measure resistance at a center of the device body;
wherein a non-local resistance signal is measured by the first and second read out electrodes at the neck and a local resistance signal is measured with the third read out electrode.

8. An electrically switchable antiferromagnetic device, the device comprising:
(a) a device body with at least one neck extending radially from the body, said body formed from crystalline FexNbS2;
(b) one or more electrodes mounted to said device body, said electrodes configured to be electrically coupled to a source of current;
(c) a first read out electrode at a first distance from a center of the device body configured to measure a resistance state of said device body at said neck; and
(d) a second read out electrode at a second distance the center of the device body;
(e) wherein an antiferromagnetic order of said device body rotates with the application of current to said write in electrode from said current source; and
(f) wherein a non-local resistance signal is measured by the first and second read out electrodes at different locations on the neck.

10. The device of claim 8, further comprising:
a third read out electrode, said third electrode configured to measure resistance at a center of the device body;
wherein a non-local resistance signal is measured by the first and second read out electrodes at the neck and a local resistance signal is measured with the third read out electrode.

12. A method of manipulating antiferromagnetic ordering in an antiferromagnetic material, the method comprising:
(a) forming an active element with a body and a neck extending radially from the body, said active element formed from a single crystal of FexNbS2;
(b) forming a plurality of write-in electrodes on said body of the active element, said electrodes electrically coupled to a source of current;
(c) forming a plurality of read-out electrodes on said neck of said active element, said electrodes;
(d) applying a current pulse to one write-in electrode; and
(e) measuring a resistance of at least one read-out electrode to determine a resistance state.

17. The method of claim 16, further comprising:
a third read out electrode, said third electrode configured to measure resistance at a center of the device body;
wherein a non-local resistance signal is measured by the first and second read out electrodes at the neck and a local resistance signal is measured with the third read out electrode.
